item.name: Alarm Notification For : ccCopyCompletion
item.description: A ccCopyCompletion trap is sent at the completion of a config-copy request. The ccCopyFailCause is not instantiated, and hence not included in a trap, when the ccCopyState is success.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cefcModuleStatusChange
item.description: This notification is generated when the value of cefcModuleOperStatus changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to update the status of the module it is managing.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cefcPowerStatusChange
item.description: The cefcFRUPowerStatusChange notification indicates that the power status of a FRU has changed. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the FRU, and the new operational-status of the FRU.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cefcFRUInserted
item.description: The cecfFRUInserted notification indicates that a FRU was inserted. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the inserted FRU, and the entPhysicalIndex of the FRU's container.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cefcFRURemoved
item.description: The cefcFRURemoved notification indicates that a FRU was removed. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the removed FRU, and the entPhysicalIndex of the FRU's container.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cefcUnrecognizedFRU
item.description: The cefcUnrecognizedFRU notification indicates that a FRU was inserted whose product ID is not supported. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the inserted FRU, the entPhysicalClass this FRU belongs to, the entPhysicalVendorType of this FRU, the entPhysicalName of the FRU, the entPhysicalModelName of the inserted FRU, and the cefcPhysicalStatus telling the reason code for sending this notification.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cefcFanTrayStatusChange
item.description: This notification is generated when the value of cefcFanTrayOperStatus changes.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cefcPowerSupplyOutputChange
item.description: The notification indicates that the power supply's output capacity has changed. This notification is triggered whenever one instance of the power supply's cefcPSOutputModeInOperation has transitioned from 'false' to 'true'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : ccStatusMemberStatusChange
item.description: A cluster member status change notification is generated whenever the value of any instance of ccClusterMemberOperStatus changes after the member is completely added to the cluster.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : ciscoConfigManEvent
item.description: Notification of a configuration management event as recorded in ccmHistoryEventTable.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification
item.description: A ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification is sent if the environmental monitor detects a testpoint reaching a critical state and is about to initiate a shutdown. This notification contains no objects so that it may be encoded and sent in the shortest amount of time possible. Even so, management applications should not rely on receiving such a notification as it may not be sent before the shutdown completes.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : ciscoEnvMonVoltageNotification
item.description: A ciscoEnvMonVoltageNotification is sent if the voltage measured at a given testpoint is outside the normal range for the testpoint (i.e. is at the warning, critical, or shutdown stage). Since such a notification is usually generated before the shutdown state is reached, it can convey more data and has a better chance of being sent than does the ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification. This notification is deprecated in favour of ciscoEnvMonVoltStatusChangeNotif.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : ciscoEnvMonTemperatureNotification
item.description: A ciscoEnvMonTemperatureNotification is sent if the temperature measured at a given testpoint is outside the normal range for the testpoint (i.e. is at the warning, critical, or shutdown stage). Since such a Notification is usually generated before the shutdown state is reached, it can convey more data and has a better chance of being sent than does the ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification. This notification is deprecated in favour of ciscoEnvMonTempStatusChangeNotif.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpmCPURisingThreshold
item.description: A cpmCPURisingThreshold notification is sent when configured rising CPU utilization threshold (cpmCPURisingThresholdValue) is reached and CPU utilization remained above the threshold for configured interval(cpmCPURisingThresholdPeriod) and such a notification is requested. The cpmProcExtUtil5SecRev and cpmProcessTimeCreated objects can be repeated multiple times in a notification indicating the top users of CPU.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpmCPUFallingThreshold
item.description: A cpmCPUFallingThresholdTrap is sent when the configured falling threshold (cpmCPURisingThresholdValue) is reached and CPU utilization remained under threshold for configured interval (cpmCPUFallingThresholdPeriod) and such a notification is requested.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : lerAlarmOn
item.description: A lerAlarmOn trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the fddimibPORTLerFlag object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB (RFC 1512) has transitioned to the true(1) state for one of its ports. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the fddimibPORTLerAlarm object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB for each port.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : lerAlarmOff
item.description: A lerAlarmOff trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the fddimibPORTLerFlag object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB (RFC 1512) has transitioned to the false(2) state for one of its ports. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the fddimibPORTLerAlarm object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB for each port.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : moduleUp
item.description: A moduleUp trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the moduleStatus object in this MIB has transitioned to the ok(2) state for one of its modules. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableModuleTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : moduleDown
item.description: A moduleDown trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the moduleStatus object in this MIB has transitioned out of the ok(2) state for one of its modules. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableModuleTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : chassisAlarmOn
item.description: A chassisAlarmOn trap signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm, chassisMinorAlarm, or chassisMajorAlarm object in this MIB has transitioned to the on(2) state. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableChassisTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : chassisAlarmOff
item.description: A chassisAlarmOff trap signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm, chassisMinorAlarm, or chassisMajorAlarm object in this MIB has transitioned to the off(1) state. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableChassisTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : ipPermitDeniedTrap
item.description: ipPermitDeniedTrap indicates that IP permit denied access happens. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableIpPermitTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : sysConfigChangeTrap
item.description: A sysConfigChange trap signifies that the system configuration in NVRAM is changed. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableConfigTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : tokenRingSoftErrExceededTrap
item.description: This trap is generated when a station local to a token ring port exceeds its Soft Error Threshold within the configured interval.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : clogMessageGenerated
item.description: When a syslog message is generated by the device a clogMessageGenerated notification is sent. The sending of these notifications can be enabled/disabled via the clogNotificationsEnabled object.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cmnMacChangedNotification
item.description: This notification is generated when there is enough MAC address information to fully occupy a maximum size SNMP trap message. This notification is also generated when there is at least one MAC address changed or removed and the amount of time elapsed from the previous notification is greater than the maximum wait time denoted by cmnNotificationInterval object. If there are more MAC addresses information than can fit into one cmmHistTrapContent object, then multiple notifications will be generated.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cmnMacMoveNotification
item.description: cmnMacMoveNotification is generated when a MAC address is moved between two interfaces.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif
item.description: cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif is sent when cmnUtilizationUtilization exceeds or equals to the cmnMACThresholdLimit for a given entPhysicalIndex.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpaeNoGuestVlanNotif
item.description: A cpaeNoGuestVlanNotif is sent if a non-802.1x supplicant is detected on a PAE port for which the value of corresponding instance of dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl is 'auto' and the value of corresponding instance of cpaeGuestVlanNumber is zero.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpaeNoAuthFailVlanNotif
item.description: A cpaeNoAuthFailVlanNotif is sent if a 802.1x supplicant fails to authenticate on a PAE port for which the value of corresponding instance of dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl is 'auto' and the value of corresponding instance of cpaePortAuthFailVlan is zero.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpsSecureMacAddrViolation
item.description: The address violation notification is generated when port security address violation is detected on a secure non-trunk, access interface (that carries a single vlan) and the cpsIfViolationAction is set to 'dropNotify'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpsTrunkSecureMacAddrViolation
item.description: The address violation notification is generated when port security address violation is detected on a secure trunk or a multi-vlan interface and the cpsIfViolationAction is set to 'dropNotify'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonConnectionChangeNotification
item.description: This notification is only valid when the RttMonRttType is 'echo' or 'pathEcho'. A rttMonConnectionChangeNotification indicates that a connection to a target (not to a hop along the path to a target) has either failed on establishment or been lost and when reestablished. Precisely, this has resulted in rttMonCtrlOperConnectionLostOccurred changing value. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonTimeoutNotification
item.description: A rttMonTimeoutNotification indicates the occurrence of a timeout for a RTT operation, and it indicates the clearing of such a condition by a subsequent RTT operation. Precisely, this has resulted in rttMonCtrlOperTimeoutOccurred changing value. When the RttMonRttType is 'pathEcho', this notification will only be sent when the timeout occurs during an operation to the target and not to a hop along the path to the target. This also applies to the clearing of the timeout. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonThresholdNotification
item.description: A rttMonThresholdNotification indicates the occurrence of a threshold violation for a RTT operation, and it indicates the previous violation has subsided for a subsequent RTT operation. Precisely, this has resulted in rttMonCtrlOperOverThresholdOccurred changing value. When the RttMonRttType is 'pathEcho', this notification will only be sent when the threshold violation occurs during an operation to the target and not to a hop along the path to the target. This also applies to the subsiding of a threshold condition. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonVerifyErrorNotification
item.description: A rttMonVerifyErrorNotification indicates the occurrence of a data corruption in an RTT operation.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonNotification
item.description: A rttMonNotification indicates the occurrence of a threshold violation, and it indicates the previous violation has subsided for a subsequent operation. When the RttMonRttType is 'pathEcho', this notification will only be sent when the threshold violation occurs during an operation to the target and not to a hop along the path to the target. This also applies to the subsiding of a threshold condition. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null. rttMonReactVar defines the type of reaction that is configured for the probe ( e.g jitterAvg, rtt etc ). In the rttMonReactTable there are trap definitions for the probes and each probe may have more than one trap definitions for various types ( e.g rtt, jitterAvg, packetLoossSD etc ). So the object rttMonReactVar indicates the type ( e.g. rtt, packetLossSD, timeout etc ) for which threshold violation traps has been generated. The object rttMonEchoAdminLSPSelector will be valid only for the probes based on 'mplsLspPingAppl' RttMonProtocol. For all other probes it will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonLpdDiscoveryNotification
item.description: A rttMonLpdDiscoveryNotification indicates that the LSP Path Discovery to the target PE has failed, and it also indicates the clearing of such condition. Precisely this has resulted in rttMonLpdGrpStatsLPDFailOccurred changing value. When the rttMonLpdGrpStatsLPDFailOccurred is 'false', the instance value for rttMonLpdGrpStatsLPDFailCause is not valid.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonLpdGrpStatusNotification
item.description: A rttMonLpdGrpStatusNotification indicates that the LPD Group status rttMonLpdGrpStatsGroupStatus has changed indicating some connectivity change to the target PE. This has resulted in rttMonLpdGrpStatsGroupStatus changing value.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : stpxInconsistencyUpdate
item.description: A stpxPortInconsistencyUpdate notification is sent by a bridge when an instance of stpxInconsistentState is created or destroyed. That is, when an inconsistency is discovered in the VLAN's Spanning Tree for a particular port, or when such an inconsistency disappears. Note that the trap is not sent if the port transitions between different types of inconsistency. The stpxInconsistentState value indicates the type of inconsistency which now exists/no longer exists for the relevant VLAN on the relevant port.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : stpxRootInconsistencyUpdate
item.description: A stpxRootInconsistencyUpdate notification is sent by a bridge when an instance of stpxRootInconsistencyState is created or destroyed. That is, when an root-inconsistency is discovered in the VLAN's or instance's Spanning Tree for a particular port, or when such an root-inconsistency disappears. For creation, the value of stpxRootInconsistencyState in the notification is true(1);for deletion, the value is false(2). The object value of stpxSpanningTreeType indicates which Spanning Tree protocol is running when an instance of stpxRootInconsistencyState is created or destroyed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : stpxLoopInconsistencyUpdate
item.description: A stpxLoopInconsistencyUpdate notification is sent by a bridge when an instance of stpxLoopInconsistencyState is created or destroyed. That is, when an loop-inconsistency is discovered in the VLAN's or instance's Spanning Tree for a particular port, or when such an loop-inconsistency disappears. For creation, the value of stpxLoopInconsistencyState in the notification is true(1);for deletion, the value is false(2). The object value of stpxSpanningTreeType indicates which Spanning Tree protocol is running when an instance of stpxLoopInconsistencyState is created or destroyed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vmVmpsChange
item.description: A VMPS change notification is generated whenever vmVmpsChanges is incremented. The IP address of the new VMPS is sent.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpConfigRevNumberError
item.description: A configuration revision number error notification signifies that a device has incremented its vtpConfigRevNumberErrors counter. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'. The device must throttle the generation of consecutive vtpConfigRevNumberError notifications so that there is at least a five-second gap between notification of this type. When notification are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time. (Note that 'generating' a notification means sending to all configured recipients.)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpConfigDigestError
item.description: A configuration digest error notification signifies that a device has incremented its vtpConfigDigestErrors counter. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'. The device must throttle the generation of consecutive vtpConfigDigestError notifications so that there is at least a five-second gap between notification of this type. When notification are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time. (Note that 'generating' a notification means sending to all configured recipients.)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpServerDisabled
item.description: A VTP Server disabled notification is generated when the local system is no longer able to function as a VTP Server because the number of defined VLANs is greater than vtpMaxVlanStorage. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpMtuTooBig
item.description: A VTP MTU tooBig notification is generated when a VLAN's MTU size is larger than can be supported either: -by one or more of its trunk ports: the included vtpVlanState has the value 'mtuTooBigForTrunk' and the included vlanTrunkPortManagementDomain is for the first (or only) trunk port, or -by the device itself: vtpVlanState has the value 'mtuTooBigForDevice' and any instance of vlanTrunkPortManagementDomain is included. Devices which have no trunk ports do not send vtpMtuTooBig notifications. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVersionOneDeviceDetected
item.description: A VTP version one device detected notification is generated by a device when: a) a management domain has been put into version 2 mode (as accessed by managementDomainVersionInUse). b) 15 minutes has passed since a). c) a version 1 PDU is detected on a trunk on the device that is in that management domain which has a lower revision number than the current configuration.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatusChange
item.description: A vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatusChange notification is generated by a device when the value of vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatus object has been changed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpLocalModeChanged
item.description: A vtpLocalModeChanged notification is generated by a device when the value of the object managementDomainLocalMode is changed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVersionInUseChanged
item.description: A vtpVersionInUseChanged notification is generated by a device when the value of the object managementDomainVersionInUse is changed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVlanCreated
item.description: A vtpVlanCreated notification is generated by a device when a VLAN is created.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVlanDeleted
item.description: A vtpVlanDeleted notification is generated by a device when a VLAN is deleted.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVlanRingNumberConflict
item.description: A VTP ring number configuration conflict notification is generated if, and only at the time when, a device learns of a conflict between: a) the ring number (vtpVlanPortLocalSegment) being used on a token ring segment attached to the port identified by ifIndex, and b) the VTP-obtained ring number (vtpVlanRingNumber) for the VLAN identified by vtpVlanIndex. When such a conflict occurs, the bridge port is put into an administrative down position until the conflict is resolved through local/network management intervention. This notification is only applicable to VLANs of type 'tokenRing'.

The cpmProcExtUtil5SecRev and cpmProcessTimeCreated objects can be repeated multiple times in a notification indicating the top users of CPU.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpmCPUFallingThreshold
item.description: A cpmCPUFallingThresholdTrap is sent when the configured falling threshold (cpmCPURisingThresholdValue) is reached and CPU utilization remained under threshold for configured interval (cpmCPUFallingThresholdPeriod) and such a notification is requested.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : lerAlarmOn
item.description: A lerAlarmOn trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the fddimibPORTLerFlag object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB (RFC 1512) has transitioned to the true(1) state for one of its ports. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the fddimibPORTLerAlarm object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB for each port.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : lerAlarmOff
item.description: A lerAlarmOff trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the fddimibPORTLerFlag object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB (RFC 1512) has transitioned to the false(2) state for one of its ports. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the fddimibPORTLerAlarm object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB for each port.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : moduleUp
item.description: A moduleUp trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the moduleStatus object in this MIB has transitioned to the ok(2) state for one of its modules. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableModuleTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : moduleDown
item.description: A moduleDown trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the moduleStatus object in this MIB has transitioned out of the ok(2) state for one of its modules. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableModuleTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : chassisAlarmOn
item.description: A chassisAlarmOn trap signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm, chassisMinorAlarm, or chassisMajorAlarm object in this MIB has transitioned to the on(2) state. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableChassisTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : chassisAlarmOff
item.description: A chassisAlarmOff trap signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm, chassisMinorAlarm, or chassisMajorAlarm object in this MIB has transitioned to the off(1) state. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableChassisTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : ipPermitDeniedTrap
item.description: ipPermitDeniedTrap indicates that IP permit denied access happens. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableIpPermitTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : sysConfigChangeTrap
item.description: A sysConfigChange trap signifies that the system configuration in NVRAM is changed. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableConfigTraps object in this MIB.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : tokenRingSoftErrExceededTrap
item.description: This trap is generated when a station local to a token ring port exceeds its Soft Error Threshold within the configured interval.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : clogMessageGenerated
item.description: When a syslog message is generated by the device a clogMessageGenerated notification is sent. The sending of these notifications can be enabled/disabled via the clogNotificationsEnabled object.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cmnMacChangedNotification
item.description: This notification is generated when there is enough MAC address information to fully occupy a maximum size SNMP trap message. This notification is also generated when there is at least one MAC address changed or removed and the amount of time elapsed from the previous notification is greater than the maximum wait time denoted by cmnNotificationInterval object. If there are more MAC addresses information than can fit into one cmmHistTrapContent object, then multiple notifications will be generated.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cmnMacMoveNotification
item.description: cmnMacMoveNotification is generated when a MAC address is moved between two interfaces.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif
item.description: cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif is sent when cmnUtilizationUtilization exceeds or equals to the cmnMACThresholdLimit for a given entPhysicalIndex.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpaeNoGuestVlanNotif
item.description: A cpaeNoGuestVlanNotif is sent if a non-802.1x supplicant is detected on a PAE port for which the value of corresponding instance of dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl is 'auto' and the value of corresponding instance of cpaeGuestVlanNumber is zero.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpaeNoAuthFailVlanNotif
item.description: A cpaeNoAuthFailVlanNotif is sent if a 802.1x supplicant fails to authenticate on a PAE port for which the value of corresponding instance of dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl is 'auto' and the value of corresponding instance of cpaePortAuthFailVlan is zero.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpsSecureMacAddrViolation
item.description: The address violation notification is generated when port security address violation is detected on a secure non-trunk, access interface (that carries a single vlan) and the cpsIfViolationAction is set to 'dropNotify'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : cpsTrunkSecureMacAddrViolation
item.description: The address violation notification is generated when port security address violation is detected on a secure trunk or a multi-vlan interface and the cpsIfViolationAction is set to 'dropNotify'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonConnectionChangeNotification
item.description: This notification is only valid when the RttMonRttType is 'echo' or 'pathEcho'. A rttMonConnectionChangeNotification indicates that a connection to a target (not to a hop along the path to a target) has either failed on establishment or been lost and when reestablished. Precisely, this has resulted in rttMonCtrlOperConnectionLostOccurred changing value. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonTimeoutNotification
item.description: A rttMonTimeoutNotification indicates the occurrence of a timeout for a RTT operation, and it indicates the clearing of such a condition by a subsequent RTT operation. Precisely, this has resulted in rttMonCtrlOperTimeoutOccurred changing value. When the RttMonRttType is 'pathEcho', this notification will only be sent when the timeout occurs during an operation to the target and not to a hop along the path to the target. This also applies to the clearing of the timeout. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonThresholdNotification
item.description: A rttMonThresholdNotification indicates the occurrence of a threshold violation for a RTT operation, and it indicates the previous violation has subsided for a subsequent RTT operation. Precisely, this has resulted in rttMonCtrlOperOverThresholdOccurred changing value. When the RttMonRttType is 'pathEcho', this notification will only be sent when the threshold violation occurs during an operation to the target and not to a hop along the path to the target. This also applies to the subsiding of a threshold condition. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonVerifyErrorNotification
item.description: A rttMonVerifyErrorNotification indicates the occurrence of a data corruption in an RTT operation.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonNotification
item.description: A rttMonNotification indicates the occurrence of a threshold violation, and it indicates the previous violation has subsided for a subsequent operation. When the RttMonRttType is 'pathEcho', this notification will only be sent when the threshold violation occurs during an operation to the target and not to a hop along the path to the target. This also applies to the subsiding of a threshold condition. If History is not being collected, the instance values for the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will not be valid. When RttMonRttType is not 'echo' or 'pathEcho' the rttMonHistoryCollectionAddress object will be null. rttMonReactVar defines the type of reaction that is configured for the probe ( e.g jitterAvg, rtt etc ). In the rttMonReactTable there are trap definitions for the probes and each probe may have more than one trap definitions for various types ( e.g rtt, jitterAvg, packetLoossSD etc ). So the object rttMonReactVar indicates the type ( e.g. rtt, packetLossSD, timeout etc ) for which threshold violation traps has been generated. The object rttMonEchoAdminLSPSelector will be valid only for the probes based on 'mplsLspPingAppl' RttMonProtocol. For all other probes it will be null.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonLpdDiscoveryNotification
item.description: A rttMonLpdDiscoveryNotification indicates that the LSP Path Discovery to the target PE has failed, and it also indicates the clearing of such condition. Precisely this has resulted in rttMonLpdGrpStatsLPDFailOccurred changing value. When the rttMonLpdGrpStatsLPDFailOccurred is 'false', the instance value for rttMonLpdGrpStatsLPDFailCause is not valid.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : rttMonLpdGrpStatusNotification
item.description: A rttMonLpdGrpStatusNotification indicates that the LPD Group status rttMonLpdGrpStatsGroupStatus has changed indicating some connectivity change to the target PE. This has resulted in rttMonLpdGrpStatsGroupStatus changing value.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : stpxInconsistencyUpdate
item.description: A stpxPortInconsistencyUpdate notification is sent by a bridge when an instance of stpxInconsistentState is created or destroyed. That is, when an inconsistency is discovered in the VLAN's Spanning Tree for a particular port, or when such an inconsistency disappears. Note that the trap is not sent if the port transitions between different types of inconsistency. The stpxInconsistentState value indicates the type of inconsistency which now exists/no longer exists for the relevant VLAN on the relevant port.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : stpxRootInconsistencyUpdate
item.description: A stpxRootInconsistencyUpdate notification is sent by a bridge when an instance of stpxRootInconsistencyState is created or destroyed. That is, when an root-inconsistency is discovered in the VLAN's or instance's Spanning Tree for a particular port, or when such an root-inconsistency disappears. For creation, the value of stpxRootInconsistencyState in the notification is true(1);for deletion, the value is false(2). The object value of stpxSpanningTreeType indicates which Spanning Tree protocol is running when an instance of stpxRootInconsistencyState is created or destroyed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : stpxLoopInconsistencyUpdate
item.description: A stpxLoopInconsistencyUpdate notification is sent by a bridge when an instance of stpxLoopInconsistencyState is created or destroyed. That is, when an loop-inconsistency is discovered in the VLAN's or instance's Spanning Tree for a particular port, or when such an loop-inconsistency disappears. For creation, the value of stpxLoopInconsistencyState in the notification is true(1);for deletion, the value is false(2). The object value of stpxSpanningTreeType indicates which Spanning Tree protocol is running when an instance of stpxLoopInconsistencyState is created or destroyed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vmVmpsChange
item.description: A VMPS change notification is generated whenever vmVmpsChanges is incremented. The IP address of the new VMPS is sent.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpConfigRevNumberError
item.description: A configuration revision number error notification signifies that a device has incremented its vtpConfigRevNumberErrors counter. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'. The device must throttle the generation of consecutive vtpConfigRevNumberError notifications so that there is at least a five-second gap between notification of this type. When notification are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time. (Note that 'generating' a notification means sending to all configured recipients.)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpConfigDigestError
item.description: A configuration digest error notification signifies that a device has incremented its vtpConfigDigestErrors counter. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'. The device must throttle the generation of consecutive vtpConfigDigestError notifications so that there is at least a five-second gap between notification of this type. When notification are throttled, they are dropped, not queued for sending at a future time. (Note that 'generating' a notification means sending to all configured recipients.)

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpServerDisabled
item.description: A VTP Server disabled notification is generated when the local system is no longer able to function as a VTP Server because the number of defined VLANs is greater than vtpMaxVlanStorage. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpMtuTooBig
item.description: A VTP MTU tooBig notification is generated when a VLAN's MTU size is larger than can be supported either: -by one or more of its trunk ports: the included vtpVlanState has the value 'mtuTooBigForTrunk' and the included vlanTrunkPortManagementDomain is for the first (or only) trunk port, or -by the device itself: vtpVlanState has the value 'mtuTooBigForDevice' and any instance of vlanTrunkPortManagementDomain is included. Devices which have no trunk ports do not send vtpMtuTooBig notifications. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVersionOneDeviceDetected
item.description: A VTP version one device detected notification is generated by a device when: a) a management domain has been put into version 2 mode (as accessed by managementDomainVersionInUse). b) 15 minutes has passed since a). c) a version 1 PDU is detected on a trunk on the device that is in that management domain which has a lower revision number than the current configuration.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatusChange
item.description: A vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatusChange notification is generated by a device when the value of vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatus object has been changed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpLocalModeChanged
item.description: A vtpLocalModeChanged notification is generated by a device when the value of the object managementDomainLocalMode is changed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVersionInUseChanged
item.description: A vtpVersionInUseChanged notification is generated by a device when the value of the object managementDomainVersionInUse is changed.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVlanCreated
item.description: A vtpVlanCreated notification is generated by a device when a VLAN is created.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVlanDeleted
item.description: A vtpVlanDeleted notification is generated by a device when a VLAN is deleted.

item.name: Alarm Notification For : vtpVlanRingNumberConflict
item.description: A VTP ring number configuration conflict notification is generated if, and only at the time when, a device learns of a conflict between: a) the ring number (vtpVlanPortLocalSegment) being used on a token ring segment attached to the port identified by ifIndex, and b) the VTP-obtained ring number (vtpVlanRingNumber) for the VLAN identified by vtpVlanIndex. When such a conflict occurs, the bridge port is put into an administrative down position until the conflict is resolved through local/network management intervention. This notification is only applicable to VLANs of type 'tokenRing'.

trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification is sent if the environmental monitor detects a testpoint reaching a critical state and is about to initiate a shutdown. This notification contains no objects so that it may be encoded and sent in the shortest amount of time possible. Even so, management applications should not rely on receiving such a notification as it may not be sent before the shutdown completes.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.4$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.4")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.4$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: VLAN's MTU size is larger than can be supported.
trigger.description: A VTP MTU tooBig notification is generated when a VLAN's MTU size is larger than can be supported either: -by one or more of its trunk ports: the included vtpVlanState has the value 'mtuTooBigForTrunk' and the included vlanTrunkPortManagementDomain is for the first (or only) trunk port, or -by the device itself: vtpVlanState has the value 'mtuTooBigForDevice' and any instance of vlanTrunkPortManagementDomain is included. Devices which have no trunk ports do not send vtpMtuTooBig notifications. Generation of this notification is suppressed if the vtpNotificationsEnabled has the value 'false'.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.6$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.6")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.6$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: vtp Version One Device has been Detected.
trigger.description: A VTP version one device detected notification is generated by a device when: a) a management domain has been put into version 2 mode (as accessed by managementDomainVersionInUse). b) 15 minutes has passed since a). c) a version 1 PDU is detected on a trunk on the device that is in that management domain which has a lower revision number than the current configuration.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.7$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.7")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.7$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: value of vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatus object has been changed.
trigger.description: A vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatusChange notification is generated by a device when the value of vlanTrunkPortDynamicStatus object has been changed.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.8$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.8")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.8$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: vtp Local Mode has been Changed.
trigger.description: A vtpLocalModeChanged notification is generated by a device when the value of the object managementDomainLocalMode is changed.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.9$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.9")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.9$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: vtp Version In Use Changed.
trigger.description: A vtpVersionInUseChanged notification is generated by a device when the value of the object managementDomainVersionInUse is changed.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.10$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.10")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.10$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: vtp Vlan Created.
trigger.description: A vtpVlanCreated notification is generated by a device when a VLAN is created.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.11$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.11")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.11$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: vtp Vlan Deleted.
trigger.description: A vtpVlanDeleted notification is generated by a device when a VLAN is deleted.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.12$\b)"].str("enterprises.9.9.46.2.0.12")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(\benterprises.9.9.46.2.0.12$\b)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: vtp Vlan Ring Number has a Conflict.
trigger.description: A VTP ring number configuration conflict notification is generated if, and only at the time when, a device learns of a conflict between: a) the ring number (vtpVlanPortLocalSegment) being used on a token ring segment attached to the port identified by ifIndex, and b) the VTP-obtained ring number (vtpVlanRingNumber) for the VLAN identified by vtpVlanIndex. When such a conflict occurs, the bridge port is put into an administrative down position until the conflict is resolved through local/network management intervention. This notification is only applicable to VLANs of type 'tokenRing'.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ccCopyCompletion$)"].str("ccCopyCompletion")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ccCopyCompletion$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: A ccCopyCompletion trap is sent at the completionof a config-copy request.
trigger.description: A ccCopyCompletion trap is sent at the completion of a config-copy request. The ccCopyFailCause is not instantiated, and hence not included in a trap, when the ccCopyState is success.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcModuleStatusChange$)"].str("cefcModuleStatusChange")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcModuleStatusChange$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: This notification is generated when the value ofcefcModuleOperStatus changes.
trigger.description: This notification is generated when the value of cefcModuleOperStatus changes. It can be utilized by an NMS to update the status of the module it is managing.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcPowerStatusChange$)"].str("cefcPowerStatusChange")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcPowerStatusChange$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: The cefcFRUPowerStatusChange notification indicates thatthe power status of a FRU has changed.
trigger.description: The cefcFRUPowerStatusChange notification indicates that the power status of a FRU has changed. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the FRU, and the new operational-status of the FRU.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcFRUInserted$)"].str("cefcFRUInserted")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcFRUInserted$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: The cecfFRUInserted notification indicates that a FRU was inserted.
trigger.description: The cecfFRUInserted notification indicates that a FRU was inserted. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the inserted FRU, and the entPhysicalIndex of the FRU's container.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcFRURemoved$)"].str("cefcFRURemoved")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcFRURemoved$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: The cefcFRURemoved notification indicates that a FRU wasremoved. The varbind for this notification indicates theentPhysicalIndex of the removed FRU, and the entPhysicalIndexof the FRU's container.
trigger.description: The cefcFRURemoved notification indicates that a FRU was removed. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the removed FRU, and the entPhysicalIndex of the FRU's container.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcUnrecognizedFRU$)"].str("cefcUnrecognizedFRU")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcUnrecognizedFRU$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: FRU was inserted whose product ID is not supported.
trigger.description: The cefcUnrecognizedFRU notification indicates that a FRU was inserted whose product ID is not supported. The varbind for this notification indicates the entPhysicalIndex of the inserted FRU, the entPhysicalClass this FRU belongs to, the entPhysicalVendorType of this FRU, the entPhysicalName of the FRU, the entPhysicalModelName of the inserted FRU, and the cefcPhysicalStatus telling the reason code for sending this notification.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcFanTrayStatusChange$)"].str("cefcFanTrayStatusChange")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcFanTrayStatusChange$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: This notification is generated when the value ofcefcFanTrayOperStatus changes.
trigger.description: This notification is generated when the value of cefcFanTrayOperStatus changes.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcPowerSupplyOutputChange$)"].str("cefcPowerSupplyOutputChange")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cefcPowerSupplyOutputChange$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: The notification indicates that the powersupply's output capacity has changed.
trigger.description: The notification indicates that the power supply's output capacity has changed. This notification is triggered whenever one instance of the power supply's cefcPSOutputModeInOperation has transitioned from 'false' to 'true'.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ccStatusMemberStatusChange$)"].str("ccStatusMemberStatusChange")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ccStatusMemberStatusChange$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: ccClusterMemberOperStatus changes after the member is completely added to the cluster.
trigger.description: A cluster member status change notification is generated whenever the value of any instance of ccClusterMemberOperStatus changes after the member is completely added to the cluster.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoConfigManEvent$)"].str("ciscoConfigManEvent")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoConfigManEvent$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: Notification of a configuration management event as recorded in ccmHistoryEventTable.
trigger.description: Notification of a configuration management event as recorded in ccmHistoryEventTable.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: Monitor detects a testpoint reaching a critical state and is about to initiate a shutdown.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification is sent if the environmental monitor detects a testpoint reaching a critical state and is about to initiate a shutdown. This notification contains no objects so that it may be encoded and sent in the shortest amount of time possible. Even so, management applications should not rely on receiving such a notification as it may not be sent before the shutdown completes.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonVoltageNotification$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonVoltageNotification")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonVoltageNotification$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: voltage measured at a given testpoint is outside the normal range for the testpoint.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonVoltageNotification is sent if the voltage measured at a given testpoint is outside the normal range for the testpoint (i.e. is at the warning, critical, or shutdown stage). Since such a notification is usually generated before the shutdown state is reached, it can convey more data and has a better chance of being sent than does the ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification. This notification is deprecated in favour of ciscoEnvMonVoltStatusChangeNotif.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonTemperatureNotification$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonTemperatureNotification")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonTemperatureNotification$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: given testpoint is outsidethe normal range for the testpoint.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonTemperatureNotification is sent if the temperature measured at a given testpoint is outside the normal range for the testpoint (i.e. is at the warning, critical, or shutdown stage). Since such a Notification is usually generated before the shutdown state is reached, it can convey more data and has a better chance of being sent than does the ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification. This notification is deprecated in favour of ciscoEnvMonTempStatusChangeNotif.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonFanNotification$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonFanNotification")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonFanNotification$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: fans in the fan array (where extant) failed.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonFanNotification is sent if any one of the fans in the fan array (where extant) fails. Since such a notification is usually generated before the shutdown state is reached, it can convey more data and has a better chance of being sent than does the ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification. This notification is deprecated in favour of ciscoEnvMonFanStatusChangeNotif.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonRedundantSupplyNotification$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonRedundantSupplyNotification")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonRedundantSupplyNotification$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: redundant power supply (where extant) fails.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonRedundantSupplyNotification is sent if the redundant power supply (where extant) fails. Since such a notification is usually generated before the shutdown state is reached, it can convey more data and has a better chance of being sent than does the ciscoEnvMonShutdownNotification. This notification is deprecated in favour of ciscoEnvMonSuppStatusChangeNotif.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonVoltStatusChangeNotif$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonVoltStatusChangeNotif")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonVoltStatusChangeNotif$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonVoltageState.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonVoltStatusChangeNotif is sent if there is change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonVoltageState.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonTempStatusChangeNotif$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonTempStatusChangeNotif")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonTempStatusChangeNotif$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonTemperatureState.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonTempStatusChangeNotif is sent if there is change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonTemperatureState.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonFanStatusChangeNotif$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonFanStatusChangeNotif")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonFanStatusChangeNotif$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonFanState.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonFanStatusChangeNotif is sent if there is change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonFanState.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonSuppStatusChangeNotif$)"].str("ciscoEnvMonSuppStatusChangeNotif")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoEnvMonSuppStatusChangeNotif$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonSupplyState.
trigger.description: A ciscoEnvMonSupplyStatChangeNotif is sent if there is change in the state of a device being monitored by ciscoEnvMonSupplyState.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashCopyCompletionTrap$)"].str("ciscoFlashCopyCompletionTrap")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashCopyCompletionTrap$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: flash copy operation Completed
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashCopyCompletionTrap is sent at the completion of a flash copy operation if such a trap was requested when the operation was initiated.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashPartitioningCompletionTrap$)"].str("ciscoFlashPartitioningCompletionTrap")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashPartitioningCompletionTrap$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: partitioning operation Complete.
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashPartitioningCompletionTrap is sent at the completion of a partitioning operation if such a trap was requested when the operation was initiated.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashMiscOpCompletionTrap$)"].str("ciscoFlashMiscOpCompletionTrap")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashMiscOpCompletionTrap$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: miscellaneous flash operation Completed.
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashMiscOpCompletionTrap is sent at the completion of a miscellaneous flash operation (enumerated in ciscoFlashMiscOpCommand) if such a trap was requested when the operation was initiated.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceChangeTrap$)"].str("ciscoFlashDeviceChangeTrap")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceChangeTrap$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: removable Flash device is inserted or removed.
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashDeviceChangeTrap is sent whenever a removable Flash device is inserted or removed.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotif$)"].str("ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotif")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotif$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: removable Flash device is inserted.
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotif notification is sent whenever a removable Flash device is inserted.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotif$)"].str("ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotif")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotif$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: removable Flash device is removed.
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotif notification is sent whenever a removable Flash device is removed.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotifRev1$)"].str("ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotifRev1")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotifRev1$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: removable Flash device is inserted.
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotif notification is sent whenever a removable Flash device is inserted ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotifRev1 depcrecates ciscoFlashDeviceInsertedNotif since it uses ciscoFlashDeviceName as a varbind which is deprecated

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotifRev1$)"].str("ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotifRev1")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotifRev1$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: removable Flash device is removed.
trigger.description: A ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotif notification is sent whenever a removable Flash device is removed. ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotifRev1 depcrecates ciscoFlashDeviceRemovedNotif since it uses ciscoFlashDeviceName as a varbind which is deprecated

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cpmCPURisingThreshold$)"].str("cpmCPURisingThreshold")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cpmCPURisingThreshold$)"].nodata(3d)}=0 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cpmCPUFallingThreshold$)"].str("cpmCPUFallingThreshold")}=0
trigger.name: CPU Utilization Threshold Reached.
trigger.description: A cpmCPURisingThreshold notification is sent when configured rising CPU utilization threshold (cpmCPURisingThresholdValue) is reached and CPU utilization remained above the threshold for configured interval(cpmCPURisingThresholdPeriod) and such a notification is requested. The cpmProcExtUtil5SecRev and cpmProcessTimeCreated objects can be repeated multiple times in a notification indicating the top users of CPU.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cpmCPUFallingThreshold$)"].str("cpmCPUFallingThreshold")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cpmCPUFallingThreshold$)"].nodata(1d)}=0
trigger.name: CPU Utilization falling below Threshold.
trigger.description: A cpmCPUFallingThresholdTrap is sent when the configured falling threshold (cpmCPURisingThresholdValue) is reached and CPU utilization remained under threshold for configured interval (cpmCPUFallingThresholdPeriod) and such a notification is requested.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(lerAlarmOn$)"].str("lerAlarmOn")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(lerAlarmOn$)"].nodata(1d)}=0
trigger.name: Ler Alarm ON.
trigger.description: A lerAlarmOn trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the fddimibPORTLerFlag object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB (RFC 1512) has transitioned to the true(1) state for one of its ports. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the fddimibPORTLerAlarm object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB for each port.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(lerAlarmOff$)"].str("lerAlarmOff")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(lerAlarmOff$)"].nodata(3d)}=0 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(lerAlarmOn$)"].str("lerAlarmOn")}=0
trigger.name: Ler Alarm OFF.
trigger.description: A lerAlarmOff trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the fddimibPORTLerFlag object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB (RFC 1512) has transitioned to the false(2) state for one of its ports. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the fddimibPORTLerAlarm object in the FDDI-SMT73-MIB for each port.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(moduleUp$)"].str("moduleUp")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(moduleUp$)"].nodata(1d)}=0
trigger.name: Module UP.
trigger.description: A moduleUp trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the moduleStatus object in this MIB has transitioned to the ok(2) state for one of its modules. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableModuleTraps object in this MIB.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(moduleDown$)"].str("moduleDown")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(moduleDown$)"].nodata(3d)}=0 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(moduleUp$)"].str("moduleUp")}=0
trigger.name: Module DOWN.
trigger.description: A moduleDown trap signifies that the agent entity has detected that the moduleStatus object in this MIB has transitioned out of the ok(2) state for one of its modules. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableModuleTraps object in this MIB.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(chassisAlarmOn$)"].str("chassisAlarmOn")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(chassisAlarmOn$)"].nodata(1d)}=0
trigger.name: Chassis Alarm ON.
trigger.description: A chassisAlarmOn trap signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm, chassisMinorAlarm, or chassisMajorAlarm object in this MIB has transitioned to the on(2) state. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableChassisTraps object in this MIB.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(chassisAlarmOff$)"].str("chassisAlarmOff")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(chassisAlarmOff$)"].nodata(3d)}=0 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(chassisAlarmOn$)"].str("chassisAlarmOn")}=0
trigger.name: Chassis Alarm OFF.
trigger.description: A chassisAlarmOff trap signifies that the agent entity has detected the chassisTempAlarm, chassisMinorAlarm, or chassisMajorAlarm object in this MIB has transitioned to the off(1) state. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableChassisTraps object in this MIB.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ipPermitDeniedTrap$)"].str("ipPermitDeniedTrap")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(ipPermitDeniedTrap$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: IP Permit Denied Access.
trigger.description: ipPermitDeniedTrap indicates that IP permit denied access happens. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableIpPermitTraps object in this MIB.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(sysConfigChangeTrap$)"].str("sysConfigChangeTrap")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(sysConfigChangeTrap$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: system configuration in NVRAM is changed.
trigger.description: A sysConfigChange trap signifies that the system configuration in NVRAM is changed. The generation of this trap can be controlled by the sysEnableConfigTraps object in this MIB.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(tokenRingSoftErrExceededTrap$)"].str("tokenRingSoftErrExceededTrap")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(tokenRingSoftErrExceededTrap$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: token ring port exceeds its Soft Error Threshold within the configured interval.
trigger.description: This trap is generated when a station local to a token ring port exceeds its Soft Error Threshold within the configured interval.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(clogMessageGenerated$)"].str("clogMessageGenerated")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(clogMessageGenerated$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: Clog Message Generated.
trigger.description: When a syslog message is generated by the device a clogMessageGenerated notification is sent. The sending of these notifications can be enabled/disabled via the clogNotificationsEnabled object.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cmnMacChangedNotification$)"].str("cmnMacChangedNotification")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cmnMacChangedNotification$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: MAC address changed or removed.
trigger.description: This notification is generated when there is enough MAC address information to fully occupy a maximum size SNMP trap message. This notification is also generated when there is at least one MAC address changed or removed and the amount of time elapsed from the previous notification is greater than the maximum wait time denoted by cmnNotificationInterval object. If there are more MAC addresses information than can fit into one cmmHistTrapContent object, then multiple notifications will be generated.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cmnMacMoveNotification$)"].str("cmnMacMoveNotification")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cmnMacMoveNotification$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: MAC address move between Interfaces.
trigger.description: cmnMacMoveNotification is generated when a MAC address is moved between two interfaces.

trigger.expression: {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif$)"].str("cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif")}=1 & {Template SNMP Traps CISCO Nodes:snmptrap["(cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif$)"].nodata(3d)}=0
trigger.name: cmnUtilizationUtilization exceeds or equals to the cmnMACThresholdLimit for a given entPhysicalIndex.
trigger.description: cmnMacThresholdExceedNotif is sent when cmnUtilizationUtilization exceeds or equals to the cmnMACThresholdLimit for a given entPhysicalIndex.

trigger.description: A cpaeNoGuestVlanNotif is sent if a non-802.1x supplicant is detected on a PAE port for which the value of corresponding instance of dot1xAuthAuthControlledPortControl is 'auto' and the value of corresponding instance of cpaeGuestVlanNumber is zero.
